    <h1 class="center">Temple</h1>
    <p>
      Dedicated to the five elements, our temple was fashioned from the raw earth of Nrityagram and fired after it was built. The temple is decorated with panels depicting the elements, dance motifs, mudras, and ghungroos. Inside is a granite rock scooped out to hold water and a flame that stays lit. And a clay mural of <a href="/protima" class="bodylink">Protima</a> offering flowers.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Temple was designed and built by Ray Meeker in 1998.
    </p>
